1. Data Cleaning and Preparation

1.1 Overall Data Structure

Metrics Distribution
- issue background (issue ID, status, summary, description)
- reporting info (full name, email, report method, report source) - request info (request ID, request title, issue type, department, subdivision, contact person)
- timeline (updated_at, created_at, acknowledged_at, reopened_at, closed_at, days until acknowledge, days until closed)
- geography (address, latitude, longitude)

  • continuous: Rating, Lat, Long, updated_at, created_at, acknowledged_at, reopened_at, closed_at, DaysUntilAcknowledged, DaysUntilClosed 
  • categorical: IssueStatus, Summary, Description, IssueAddress, RequestTypeTitle, IssueType, Department, Subdivision, ContactGroupPerson, ReportMethod, FullName, Email, ReportSource
  • factors: IssueStatus, RequestTypeTitle, IssueType, Department, Subdivision, ContactGroupPerson, ReportMethod, ReportSource, Rating

add dfsummary

1.2 Missing Data

  • 8 features exhibit meaningful missingness: reopened_at, DaysUntilAcknowledged, acknowledged_at, Summary, ReportSource, Subdivision, ContactGroupPerson, DaysUntilClosed, closed_at.
  • issues are almost never being reopened (99%), mostly not acknowledged (61%), missing details like summary/source/subdivision (8-17%), lack a contact person (2%) or are not closed (2%)
  • why are issues not being acknowledged?

2. Exploratory Data Analysis

2.1 Group existing and create new features

  1. Categorical columns to be factorized: “RequestTypeTitle”, “IssueType”, “Department”, “Subdivision”, “ContactGroupPerson”, “ReportMethod”, “ReportSource”, “Rating”
  2. Numerical metrics: updated, created, acknowledged, reopened, closed in datetime format so need to convert to numeric for calculation
  • updated-created (DaysUntilUpdated), acknowledged-created (DaysUntilAcknowledged), reopened-created (DaysUntilReopened), closed-created (DaysUntilClosed)
  • closed-updated (DaysSinceUpdated), closed-acknowledged (DaysSinceAcknowledged), closed-reopened (DaysSinceReopened), closed-created (DaysUntilClosed)
  1. Geographical terms: address, lat, long
factors <- c("RequestTypeTitle", "IssueType", "Department", "Subdivision", "ContactGroupPerson", "ReportMethod", "ReportSource", "Rating")
# also factorize columns
for (col in factors) {
  # Get the column as a factor
  data[[col]] <- as.factor(data[[col]])
}

2.4 Time to N

  • when summarizing factor columns by the average days taken to close issues, the issues that took the longest time to close were related to Vehicles, Cable Services, Infrastructure, Permits, OIT, P&Z, and Constituent Services

  • why do vehicles and cable services take so long to close?

factors <- c("IssueStatus", "RequestTypeTitle", "IssueType", "Department", "Subdivision", "ContactGroupPerson", "ReportMethod", "ReportSource")
for (col in factors) {
  sorted_table <- data %>% 
    group_by(data[[col]]) %>% 
    summarise(mean_days = mean(DaysUntilClosed, na.rm = TRUE), sd_days = sd(DaysUntilClosed, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
    arrange(desc(mean_days)) %>% 
    rename(!!col := `data[[col]]`) 
  #cat("Column:", col, "\n")
  print(sorted_table)
}
